{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1800,"text":"So there are lands\nfew and far between on Earth itself"},{"time":5360,"text":"that are hospitable to humans\nby any measure,"},{"time":9440,"text":"but survive we have."},{"time":11800,"text":"Our primitive ancestors, when they found\ntheir homes and livelihood endangered,"},{"time":16079,"text":"they dared to make their way\ninto unfamiliar territories"},{"time":19240,"text":"in search of better opportunities."},{"time":21760,"text":"And as the descendants of these explorers,"},{"time":24000,"text":"we have their nomadic blood\ncoursing through our own veins."},{"time":28040,"text":"But at the same time,"},{"time":29520,"text":"distracted by our bread and circuses"},{"time":31640,"text":"and embroiled in the wars\nthat we have waged on each other,"},{"time":35840,"text":"it seems that we have forgotten\nthis desire to explore."},{"time":40320,"text":"We, as a species, we're evolved uniquely"},{"time":44960,"text":"for Earth, on Earth, and by Earth,"},{"time":49680,"text":"and so content are we\nwith our living conditions"},{"time":52840,"text":"that we have grown complacent\nand just too busy"},{"time":56280,"text":"to notice that its resources are finite,"},{"time":58760,"text":"and that our Sun's life is also finite."},{"time":62400,"text":"While Mars and all the movies\nmade in its name"},{"time":65200,"text":"have reinvigorated\nthe ethos for space travel,"},{"time":68240,"text":"few of us seem to truly realize\nthat our species' fragile constitution"},{"time":73640,"text":"is woefully unprepared\nfor long duration journeys into space."}]},{"cues":[{"time":78160,"text":"Let us take a trek\nto your local national forest"},{"time":80440,"text":"for a quick reality check."},{"time":82280,"text":"So just a quick show of hands here:"},{"time":84000,"text":"how many of you think you would be able\nto survive in this lush wilderness"},{"time":87600,"text":"for a few days?"},{"time":90000,"text":"Well, that's a lot of you."},{"time":91320,"text":"How about a few weeks?"},{"time":94000,"text":"That's a decent amount."},{"time":95280,"text":"How about a few months?"},{"time":97600,"text":"That's pretty good too."},{"time":99120,"text":"Now, let us imagine\nthat this local national forest"},{"time":101800,"text":"experiences an eternal winter."},{"time":105360,"text":"Same questions: how many of you think you\nwould be able to survive for a few days?"},{"time":110280,"text":"That's quite a lot."},{"time":111720,"text":"How about a few weeks?"},{"time":114400,"text":"So for a fun twist, let us imagine\nthat the only source of water available"},{"time":119120,"text":"is trapped as frozen blocks\nmiles below the surface."},{"time":123080,"text":"Soil nutrients are so minimal\nthat no vegetation can be found,"},{"time":127200,"text":"and of course hardly any atmosphere\nexists to speak of."}]},{"cues":[{"time":133240,"text":"Such examples are only a few\nof the many challenges we would face"},{"time":137400,"text":"on a planet like Mars."},{"time":140000,"text":"So how do we steel ourselves for voyages\nwhose destinations are so far removed"},{"time":145200,"text":"from a tropical vacation?"},{"time":147520,"text":"Will we continuously ship supplies\nfrom Planet Earth?"},{"time":150880,"text":"Build space elevators,\nor impossible miles of transport belts"},{"time":154360,"text":"that tether your planet of choice\nto our home planet?"},{"time":158160,"text":"And how do we grow things like food\nthat grew up on Earth like us?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":165080,"text":"But I'm getting ahead of myself."},{"time":167560,"text":"In our species' journey\nto find a new home under a new sun,"},{"time":171720,"text":"we are more likely than not\ngoing to be spending much time"},{"time":175600,"text":"in the journey itself,"},{"time":177840,"text":"in space,"},{"time":179480,"text":"on a ship, a hermetic flying can,"},{"time":183120,"text":"possibly for many generations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":185480,"text":"The longest continuous amount of time\nthat any human has spent in space"},{"time":188920,"text":"is in the vicinity of 12 to 14 months."},{"time":192600,"text":"From astronauts' experiences in space,"},{"time":194960,"text":"we know that spending time\nin a microgravity environment"},{"time":198760,"text":"means bone loss, muscle atrophy,\ncardiovascular problems,"},{"time":203360,"text":"among many other complications"},{"time":204960,"text":"that range for the physiological\nto the psychological."},{"time":209200,"text":"And what about macrogravity,"},{"time":210640,"text":"or any other variation\nin gravitational pull"},{"time":213160,"text":"of the planet that we find ourselves on?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":216560,"text":"In short, our cosmic voyages\nwill be fraught with dangers"},{"time":220120,"text":"both known and unknown."},{"time":222960,"text":"So far we've been looking to this\nnew piece of mechanical technology"},{"time":227000,"text":"or that great next generation robot"},{"time":229280,"text":"as part of a lineup to ensure\nour species safe passage in space."},{"time":233600,"text":"Wonderful as they are,\nI believe the time has come"},{"time":236560,"text":"for us to complement\nthese bulky electronic giants"},{"time":240840,"text":"with what nature has already invented:"},{"time":244320,"text":"the microbe,"},{"time":245720,"text":"a single-celled organism that is itself\na self-generating, self-replenishing,"},{"time":250960,"text":"living machine."},{"time":252760,"text":"It requires fairly little to maintain,"},{"time":255200,"text":"offers much flexibility in design"},{"time":257120,"text":"and only asks to be carried\nin a single plastic tube."}]},{"cues":[{"time":261399,"text":"The field of study that has enabled us\nto utilize the capabilities of the microbe"},{"time":265280,"text":"is known as synthetic biology."},{"time":267520,"text":"It comes from molecular biology,\nwhich has given us antibiotics, vaccines"},{"time":271560,"text":"and better ways to observe\nthe physiological nuances"},{"time":274880,"text":"of the human body."},{"time":276520,"text":"Using the tools of synthetic biology,"},{"time":278520,"text":"we can now edit the genes\nof nearly any organism,"},{"time":281480,"text":"microscopic or not,"},{"time":283440,"text":"with incredible speed and fidelity."},{"time":286760,"text":"Given the limitations\nof our man-made machines,"},{"time":289680,"text":"synthetic biology will be a means for us\nto engineer not only our food,"},{"time":293680,"text":"our fuel and our environment,"},{"time":296440,"text":"but also ourselves"},{"time":298760,"text":"to compensate\nfor our physical inadequacies"},{"time":301400,"text":"and to ensure our survival in space."}]},{"cues":[{"time":305000,"text":"To give you an example"},{"time":306240,"text":"of how we can use synthetic biology\nfor space exploration,"},{"time":309080,"text":"let us return to the Mars environment."},{"time":312160,"text":"The Martian soil composition is similar\nto that of Hawaiian volcanic ash,"},{"time":316920,"text":"with trace amounts of organic material."},{"time":319400,"text":"Let's say, hypothetically,"},{"time":321680,"text":"what if martian soil\ncould actually support plant growth"},{"time":324440,"text":"without using Earth-derived nutrients?"},{"time":327360,"text":"The first question\nwe should probably ask is,"},{"time":329480,"text":"how would we make\nour plants cold-tolerant?"},{"time":331880,"text":"Because, on average,\nthe temperature on Mars"},{"time":334000,"text":"is a very uninviting\nnegative 60 degrees centigrade."},{"time":338000,"text":"The next question we should ask is,"},{"time":339800,"text":"how do we make\nour plants drought-tolerant?"},{"time":342280,"text":"Considering that most of the water\nthat forms as frost"},{"time":345120,"text":"evaporates more quickly\nthan I can say the word \"evaporate.\""},{"time":349120,"text":"Well, it turns out\nwe've already done things like this."},{"time":352480,"text":"By borrowing genes\nfor anti-freeze protein from fish"},{"time":355800,"text":"and genes for drought tolerance\nfrom other plants like rice"},{"time":359000,"text":"and then stitching them\ninto the plants that need them,"},{"time":361720,"text":"we now have plants that can tolerate\nmost droughts and freezes."},{"time":365480,"text":"They're known on Earth as GMOs,"},{"time":368120,"text":"or genetically modified organisms,"},{"time":370680,"text":"and we rely on them to feed\nall the mouths of human civilization."},{"time":376160,"text":"Nature does stuff like this already,"},{"time":379600,"text":"without our help."},{"time":381160,"text":"We have simply found\nmore precise ways to do it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":385480,"text":"So why would we want to change\nthe genetic makeup of plants for space?"},{"time":390120,"text":"Well, to not do so\nwould mean needing to engineer"},{"time":393720,"text":"endless acres of land\non an entirely new planet"},{"time":397160,"text":"by releasing trillions of gallons\nof atmospheric gasses"},{"time":400680,"text":"and then constructing\na giant glass dome to contain it all."},{"time":404480,"text":"It's an unrealistic engineering enterprise"},{"time":406560,"text":"that quickly becomes\na high-cost cargo transport mission."},{"time":411240,"text":"One of the best ways to ensure"},{"time":412720,"text":"that we will have the food supplies\nand the air that we need"},{"time":415840,"text":"is to bring with us organisms\nthat have been engineered"},{"time":418960,"text":"to adapt to new and harsh environments."},{"time":422760,"text":"In essence, using engineered organisms\nto help us terraform a planet"},{"time":426760,"text":"both in the short and long term."},{"time":430400,"text":"These organisms can then also\nbe engineered to make medicine or fuel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":435920,"text":"So we can use synthetic biology\nto bring highly engineered plants with us,"},{"time":439680,"text":"but what else can we do?"},{"time":441880,"text":"Well, I mentioned earlier\nthat we, as a species,"},{"time":444760,"text":"were evolved uniquely for planet Earth."},{"time":447800,"text":"That fact has not changed much\nin the last five minutes"},{"time":450440,"text":"that you were sitting here\nand I was standing there."},{"time":453480,"text":"And so, if we were to dump\nany of us on Mars right this minute,"},{"time":457200,"text":"even given ample food, water, air"},{"time":460720,"text":"and a suit,"},{"time":461960,"text":"we are likely to experience\nvery unpleasant health problems"},{"time":465360,"text":"from the amount of ionizing radiation\nthat bombards the surface"},{"time":468680,"text":"of planets like Mars that have little\nor nonexistent atmosphere."},{"time":473280,"text":"Unless we plan\nto stay holed up underground"},{"time":475320,"text":"for the duration of our stay\non every new planet,"},{"time":478480,"text":"we must find better ways\nof protecting ourselves"},{"time":481080,"text":"without needing to resort\nto wearing a suit of armor"},{"time":483760,"text":"that weighs something\nequal to your own body weight,"},{"time":486240,"text":"or needing to hide behind a wall of lead."}]},{"cues":[{"time":490240,"text":"So let us appeal\nto nature for inspiration."},{"time":494200,"text":"Among the plethora of life here on Earth,"},{"time":496320,"text":"there's a subset of organisms\nknown as extremophiles,"},{"time":499200,"text":"or lovers of extreme living conditions,"},{"time":501200,"text":"if you'll remember\nfrom high school biology."},{"time":503680,"text":"And among these organisms is a bacterium\nby the name of Deinococcus radiodurans."},{"time":509040,"text":"It is known to be able to withstand cold,\ndehydration, vacuum, acid,"},{"time":514440,"text":"and, most notably, radiation."},{"time":517440,"text":"While its radiation\ntolerance mechanisms are known,"},{"time":520159,"text":"we have yet to adapt\nthe relevant genes to mammals."},{"time":523520,"text":"To do so is not particularly easy."},{"time":526160,"text":"There are many facets\nthat go into its radiation tolerance,"},{"time":529000,"text":"and it's not as simple\nas transferring one gene."},{"time":531960,"text":"But given a little bit of human ingenuity"},{"time":535240,"text":"and a little bit of time,"},{"time":536520,"text":"I think to do so is not very hard either."},{"time":540000,"text":"Even if we borrow just a fraction\nof its ability to tolerate radiation,"},{"time":546400,"text":"it would be infinitely better\nthan what we already have,"},{"time":549440,"text":"which is just the melanin in our skin."},{"time":552560,"text":"Using the tools of synthetic biology,"},{"time":554600,"text":"we can harness Deinococcus\nradiodurans' ability"},{"time":557640,"text":"to thrive under otherwise\nvery lethal doses of radiation."},{"time":563760,"text":"As difficult as it is to see,"},{"time":565920,"text":"homo sapiens, that is humans,"},{"time":569200,"text":"evolves every day,"},{"time":571520,"text":"and still continues to evolve."},{"time":574360,"text":"Thousands of years of human evolution"},{"time":576160,"text":"has not only given us\nhumans like Tibetans,"},{"time":579160,"text":"who can thrive in low-oxygen conditions,"},{"time":581760,"text":"but also Argentinians,\nwho can ingest and metabolize arsenic,"},{"time":586720,"text":"the chemical element\nthat can kill the average human being."},{"time":590360,"text":"Every day, the human body evolves\nby accidental mutations"},{"time":594080,"text":"that equally accidentally\nallow certain humans"},{"time":596960,"text":"to persevere in dismal situations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":600160,"text":"But, and this is a big but,"},{"time":603480,"text":"such evolution requires two things\nthat we may not always have,"},{"time":607680,"text":"or be able to afford,"},{"time":610120,"text":"and they are death and time."},{"time":613560,"text":"In our species' struggle\nto find our place in the universe,"},{"time":616600,"text":"we may not always have the time necessary"},{"time":619080,"text":"for the natural evolution\nof extra functions"},{"time":621640,"text":"for survival on non-Earth planets."},{"time":624360,"text":"We're living in what E.O. Wilson\nhas termed the age of gene circumvention,"},{"time":628880,"text":"during which we remedy our genetic defects\nlike cystic fibrosis or muscular dystrophy"},{"time":634280,"text":"with temporary external supplements."},{"time":637960,"text":"But with every passing day,"},{"time":639520,"text":"we approach the age\nof volitional evolution,"},{"time":642720,"text":"a time during which we as a species"},{"time":644720,"text":"will have the capacity to decide\nfor ourselves our own genetic destiny."},{"time":650720,"text":"Augmenting the human body\nwith new abilities"},{"time":653080,"text":"is no longer a question of how,"},{"time":655920,"text":"but of when."}]},{"cues":[{"time":658240,"text":"Using synthetic biology"},{"time":659520,"text":"to change the genetic makeup\nof any living organisms,"},{"time":662640,"text":"especially our own,"},{"time":663880,"text":"is not without its moral\nand ethical quandaries."},{"time":667280,"text":"Will engineering ourselves\nmake us less human?"},{"time":670960,"text":"But then again, what is humanity"},{"time":673240,"text":"but star stuff\nthat happens to be conscious?"},{"time":677200,"text":"Where should human genius direct itself?"},{"time":680640,"text":"Surely it is a bit of a waste\nto sit back and marvel at it."},{"time":685800,"text":"How do we use our knowledge"},{"time":687160,"text":"to protect ourselves\nfrom the external dangers"},{"time":690440,"text":"and then protect ourselves from ourselves?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":694400,"text":"I pose these questions"},{"time":695840,"text":"not to engender the fear of science"},{"time":698040,"text":"but to bring to light\nthe many possibilities"},{"time":700440,"text":"that science has afforded\nand continues to afford us."},{"time":704760,"text":"We must coalesce as humans\nto discuss and embrace the solutions"},{"time":708760,"text":"not only with caution"},{"time":710640,"text":"but also with courage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":714200,"text":"Mars is a destination,"},{"time":718440,"text":"but it will not be our last."},{"time":721000,"text":"Our true final frontier\nis the line we must cross"},{"time":723880,"text":"in deciding what we can and should make\nof our species' improbable intelligence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":729880,"text":"Space is cold, brutal and unforgiving."},{"time":735120,"text":"Our path to the stars\nwill be rife with trials"},{"time":737560,"text":"that will bring us to question\nnot only who we are"},{"time":740560,"text":"but where we will be going."},{"time":743160,"text":"The answers will lie in our choice\nto use or abandon the technology"},{"time":746760,"text":"that we have gleaned from life itself,"},{"time":748880,"text":"and it will define us for the remainder\nof our term in this universe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":752760,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":754000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}